=== 8.5 The Code: FFN in Python

GELU is the activation function used in GPT-2.
For large positive stem:[x], GELU approaches stem:[x] — the value passes through.
For large negative stem:[x], it approaches 0 — the value is suppressed.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/microgpt.py[tag=activations]
----

`gelu-matrix` applies the scalar GELU to every element of a matrix.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/microgpt.py[tag=ffn]
----

`add-bias` broadcasts a bias vector stem:[b] across all rows of a matrix stem:[M].

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/microgpt.py[tag=ffn]
----

`make-ffn-params` allocates and initializes the four parameters: stem:[W_1] expands the model dimension stem:[d] to stem:[4d]; stem:[W_2] contracts it back.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/microgpt.py[tag=ffn]
----

`ffn-forward` composes the operations in the order prescribed by the formula.

